HEADWORD: defrock
<hw>defrock</hw> <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To divest of the frock, <it>i.
e.</it> to deprive (a priest, minister, etc.) of official ecclesiastical
authority; -- of church officials.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> unfrock.</syn>⟦br⟧
